  "verdict": "data_limited (range- and amplitude-limited, honestly quantified). The FULL NICER Vela archive is now reduced (665 obs -> 491 usable -> 240 per-obs detections -> 119 piecewise-coherent segments, 108 fully coherent), superseding the single-obs PG.06b proof (whose F0=11.19275 'detection' is corrected: the true Vela F0 there is 11.18617 Hz). SANITY GATE: the published glitch steps are reproduced (2019, 2021; skipped: none; 2024 window not reducible -- NICER post-2024 coverage is ~150 s snapshots). Achieved ln(tau) reach: 2019: 2.17, 2021: 1.38 comb periods -- all BELOW the 2.8-period localisation gate (first usable NICER obs is 3.4 d (2019) / 7 d (2021) post-glitch; the sub-day early window that would clear the gate is not in the archive), and the concatenated ln-tau stack (2.17 periods, p=0.05, shuffle p=0.31) buys amplitude, not range (PG.06). No preregistered escalation fires (comb p = 2019: 0.014, 2021: 0.731). AUDIT FLAG -- 2019: raw comb_p=0.014 (kernel smallest-p) but Bonferroni x10 = 0.14, shuffle p=0.40 (no ln-tau phase coherence) and reach 2.17 < 2.8 -- an audit-level chance feature, not a candidate (prereg escalation needs p<0.01 + shuffle<0.05 + gate). Surrogate-calibrated injection at the real sampling and real noise amplitudes: 2019: eps_50=0.55/eps_90=n/r, 2021: eps_50=n/r/eps_90=n/r (predicted eps~0.0173 -> chance level everywhere; n/r = not reached below eps=1). So the full ~2.6-GB (665-obs) reduction delivers the first X-ray nu(t) recovery test of the kernel comb, whose sensitivity never reaches 90% below eps=1 (range-blind, PG.06) -- an honest bounded null, NOT a well-powered kill (prereg: data_limited_if reach < 2.8 or predicted-eps power < 0.5). No claim; firewall intact."
